      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation test samples representative of the device population and operating fluid; sample size sufficient for statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "Five pump units from the same manufacturing batch used for in-vitro validation. Bovine blood with haematocrit 38 ± 2 % used as working fluid, consistent with ISO 10993-4 guidance for haemocompatibility testing. Sample representativeness confirmed for adult normative range."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation input parameters (geometry, boundary conditions, fluid properties) equivalent to experimental conditions within documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "CAD geometry used in simulation derived from coordinate measurements of physical test articles (CMM report CMM-2023-012). Fluid properties (density 1050 kg/m³, dynamic viscosity 3.5 mPa·s) matched to measured bovine blood properties at 37 °C. Inlet velocity profiles mapped from PIV measurements. Equivalency confirmed for adult validation campaign."
